\backslash
gls{mlpg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 method, the basis and weight functions have limited spatial support and
 connectivity is determined by the overlapping support regions of the basis
 and weight functions.
 While the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{mlpg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 solution can still exhibit oscillations as in the collocation approach,
 the additional freedom to specify the weight functions independent of the
 basis functions allows for the use of common stabilization techniques used
 in other weighted residual methods, such as the streamline upwind Petrov-Galerk
in (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{supg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

