\begin_layout Standard
Transport codes have several features that require special attention when
 applying meshless methods:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The advective streaming term may necessitate stabilization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Boundary conditions should be accurately represented.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The material properties can be variable in space.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Due to the dependence on space, energy and direction, the number of unknowns
 is much higher than in many other applications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Particle balance should be preserved if possible.
 
\end_layout

