\begin_layout Subsubsection
Parallel performance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Due to the shared-memory model of the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{mlpg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 code, the number of processors for which the code can be tested is limited.
 The parallelism does not involve heavy communication between processes
 for the parallel portions of the code, so good efficiency is expected for
 these portions of the code.
 However, there are some sections of the code, including the initialization
 of the spatial geometry and the outer 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{gmres}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 solver, are run in serial and could have an impact on parallel performance.
 The code is not heavily optimized for parallel performance, and so while
 these results do show good speedup for some cases, near-optimal speedup
 is not expected.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To test the parallel performance, the Kobayashi problem from Sec.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:kobayashi"

\end_inset

 with scattering is run in parallel for 1, 2, 4 and 8 processors for between
 1000 and 64000 points with the same problem parameters as in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:general-parameters-steady"

\end_inset

, except with 128 directions to decrease the total runtime of the parallel
 tests.
 The efficiency of the parallelism is calculated as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
E_{p}=\frac{T_{1}}{pT_{p}},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{p}$
\end_inset

 is the execution time of the problem on 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 processors.
 The efficiency is calculated for each of the spatial initialization step
 (which is dominated by the integration of the basis and weight functions),
 the initialization of the preconditioners and solution of the operator
 equations, and the total time.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:parallel-efficiency-kobayashi-mls"

\end_inset

