 steps is around twice as high for the solver without preconditioning.
 This problem requires around 20 applications of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 operator.
 For a problem that requires many more applications of this operator, such
 as a problem with high scattering ratios, the fixed cost of initialization
 of the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{ilut}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 matrices and low cost of the solution step for the preconditioned system
 would be much more efficient.
 
