\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 is a scaling factor.
 This continues until some maximum distance between points, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta r_{max}$
\end_inset

 is reached, at which point the scaling stops but the concentric rings of
 points continue.
 Points outside the problem boundaries are discarded and the boundaries
 are lined with points approximately 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta r_{max}$
\end_inset

