\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:manufactured-heat-source"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:manufactured-heat-temp"

\end_inset

, the temperature should be function with at least a nonzero first derivative.
 If the conduction coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 is spatially-dependent, the derivative of 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 is also required.
 The conduction coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 may also be spatially dependent.
 See Ref.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
