\end_layout

\end_inset

), regions of (usually constant) material are defined by analytic surfaces,
 such as planes, spheres and cylinders.
 The 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{csg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 can be used in Monte Carlo simulations for tracking particles through the
 problem domain by calculating which region a particle is located in, the
 distance in a given direction to the next surface, and the reflection angle
 off of a surface where applicable.
 For the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{mlpg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 transport equations, a 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
gls{csg}
\end_layout

\end_inset

